    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.20" />
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">20</fw>

                <p>I was with Custer's command for only five days during the summer of 1876. Two days were spent in camp, and three with the command on the march to the site of the fight. At the time of the fight I came to the top of the buttes overlooking the location of the present Government farm house in the district of the Reservation which has been named for Major Reno,&#8212; there I stopped and fired several shots into the Sioux camp down below. There were many Sioux and I thought that was my last day, but I am here now and alive.</p>
                <closer>
                                                                    <figure><graphic url="nei.J4a.4.20"/>
                                                                        <figDesc>Curley's thumb print</figDesc>
                                                                        <p>his mark</p>
                                                                    </figure>


                    <dateline>November 14, 1916.</dateline>                      <signed>Curley</signed>


                    Witnesses:
                    
                    <signed>James Laforge</signed>
                    Interpreter, Crow Agency, Montana.
                    
                    <signed>Lant Shane</signed>
                    Farmer, Reno District.
                </closer>

            </div1>
        </body>
        
